    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is attributed to the standardized single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol and is considered acceptable given that (a) the test condition is directly representative of the COU, (b) all quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, MAPE < 10%) are satisfied across all three QoIs at both laboratories, and (c) model influence and decision consequence are both classified as Medium. The overall credibility package supports acceptance of the FEA modeling framework for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
